), customs and passport control zones. Access to these zones, in contrast to restricted access zones, is free, however, being in them is allowed only for the purpose determined by the purpose of the zone (crossing a water barrier, boarding a train or disembarking from it, passing passport or customs control). If you are in such zones without a specific purpose, a citizen can be removed from there, and in established cases, he can be held accountable. The Thompson submachine gun is an American submachine gun invented in 1918 John Tagliaferro Thompson. This weapon gained its fame during Prohibition in the United States, becoming the most common and favorite weapon not only among police officers, but also members of various American criminal groups [17].